Day 1 (October 25): Arrival in Paris and check-in to your hotel. Spend the afternoon exploring the Latin Quarter, and enjoy a Seine River Cruise in the evening.

Day 2 (October 26): Visit the Louvre Museum in the morning, and then head to the Montmartre neighborhood for lunch and exploration. In the evening, attend the Paris Jazz Festival at Parc Floral de Paris.

Day 3 (October 27): Take a day trip to the Palace of Versailles, and enjoy the scenic gardens and fountain shows. Return to Paris in the evening and enjoy dinner at a classic French bistro.

Day 4 (October 28): Spend the day exploring the Musée d'Orsay and the nearby Tuileries Garden. In the evening, enjoy a wine tasting and dinner at a wine bar in the Marais neighborhood.

Day 5 (October 29): Visit the iconic Eiffel Tower and enjoy the stunning views of the city. In the evening, attend a cabaret show at the world-famous Moulin Rouge.

Day 6 (October 30): Explore the trendy Le Marais neighborhood and its fashionable boutiques and art galleries. In the evening, enjoy a dinner cruise on the Seine River.

Day 7 (October 31): Spend the morning visiting the historic Notre-Dame Cathedral and the nearby Sainte-Chapelle. In the evening, enjoy a farewell dinner at a Michelin-starred restaurant and celebrate the birthday with a special cake and champagne.

This itinerary provides a mix of culture, history, and entertainment, and takes into account the weather forecast and local events schedule. However, feel free to adjust it according to your preferences and interests. Bon voyage and happy birthday!
